race.comment: JACKPOT STAR (4) brings strong form scoring three back at Nowra before placing twice in a row with the most recent over 1200m at Wagga. Maps well and is in sharp local hands. Hard to beat in a suitable race. KREON (5) comes out of the same race and got too far back. Peaks now and has plenty up the sleeve. The local gets Schofield and is also suited. Feared. CRAFT (6) resumes for the Nick Olive yard and will race over further. His best efforts would see him very competitive, and he's prepared with two Canberra trials. Has the rail and Collett's engagement sparks interest. THE MONA LISA (11) resumes off an easy 58 win here. Usually needs a run or two but draws low and is worth keeping onside.
